net.smartcosmos.model.base

Enum EntityReferenceType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EntityReferenceType>
      • net.smartcosmos.model.base.EntityReferenceType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<EntityReferenceType>

    public enum EntityReferenceType
extends Enum<EntityReferenceType>
    Represents a specific type of platform entity in a generic operation. Instead of defining many different entity specific operations, a singular operation is typically defined by the platform where one of the mandatory parameters is an EntityReferenceType coupled with a referenceUrn. This reduces the number of API methods to learn, and provides an easy extension mechanism when new types of entities are defined in future releases.

    As a concrete example, consider a IRelationship used to define some arbitrary type of connection between any two existing entities defined in the system. As new entity types are added to the system, no additional work is required to support those entities so that they too can participate in relationships.
